  <div class="mb-12">
    <span class="text-sm text-emerald-600 font-bold uppercase tracking-widest">Comparison · Updated April 2026</span>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold mt-2 mb-6">Preply vs iTalki vs Cambly: The Ultimate 3-Way Comparison</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">They are the three giants of the online tutoring world. But which one is actually worth your time and money? We break down the data to help you decide.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-slate-800/40 border border-slate-700 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">The Quick Verdict</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Choose <strong>iTalki</strong> if you want the absolute lowest prices and most specific tutor expertise. Choose <strong>Preply</strong> if you want a structured, academic environment with great tracking tools. Choose <strong>Cambly</strong> if you want 24/7 on-demand conversation practice without having to book in advance.</p>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Online Tutoring in 2026: Where These Three Fit</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Online language learning has grown fast over the last few years. Hundreds of smaller platforms exist, but Preply, iTalki, and Cambly are still the three most students compare. Each one takes a different approach to teaching, so the "best" platform depends on how you like to learn.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Below we look past the marketing, at actual user experience, hidden costs, and teacher quality on each platform. Whether you are a complete beginner or already advanced, one of these three is likely the best starting point.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-16 mb-6">1. iTalki: The Custom Marketplace</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6 leading-relaxed">iTalki is the world's largest marketplace for language tutors. It does not provide its own curriculum; instead, it provides a platform where independent teachers can offer their services. This leads to an incredible amount of variety. You can find everything from university professors to casual conversation partners.</p>
  
  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">Pros of iTalki</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
    <li><strong>Price Variety:</strong> Lessons start as low as $4 or $5 per hour.</li>
    <li><strong>Specialized Tutors:</strong> Find teachers who specialize in IELTS, TOEFL, or specific business industries.</li>
    <li><strong>Community Features:</strong> Free language exchange and writing correction tools.</li>
    <li><strong>No Subscriptions:</strong> You only pay for the lessons you book.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">Cons of iTalki</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
    <li><strong>Variable Quality:</strong> Since anyone can apply to be a "Community Tutor," you have to be careful about who you book.</li>
    <li><strong>No Unified Curriculum:</strong> You and your tutor have to decide what to study.</li>
    <li><strong>Interface:</strong> Can feel a bit overwhelming for new users.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-16 mb-6">2. Preply: The Structured Classroom</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Preply feels more like a modern digital school than a marketplace. While it also features independent tutors, the platform provides a lot more structure. They have an integrated virtual classroom, a specific curriculum for different goals, and AI-powered tools that track your progress.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">Pros of Preply</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
    <li><strong>Professional Environment:</strong> The integrated classroom is one of the best in the industry.</li>
    <li><strong>Matching Algorithm:</strong> Helps you find the right tutor based on your goals and personality.</li>
    <li><strong>Corporate Focus:</strong> Excellent for business English and professional development.</li>
    <li><strong>Progress Tracking:</strong> Clear reports on how many words you have learned and hours you have studied.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">Cons of Preply</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
    <li><strong>Subscription Model:</strong> You have to buy a certain number of hours per month, which can feel restrictive.</li>
    <li><strong>Trial Lesson Policy:</strong> Trial lessons are not free for the tutors, which is a point of controversy in the community.</li>
    <li><strong>Higher Prices:</strong> Generally more expensive than the budget options on iTalki.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-16 mb-6">3. Cambly: The On-Demand Partner</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Cambly's unique selling point is its "On-Demand" feature. You do not have to book a lesson in advance. You can simply open the app, hit a button, and be talking to a native speaker in seconds. It is the closest thing to "immersion in your pocket."</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">Pros of Cambly</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
    <li><strong>Instant Access:</strong> Perfect for people with unpredictable schedules.</li>
    <li><strong>Native Speakers Only:</strong> Every tutor on Cambly is a native speaker from the US, UK, Canada, or Australia.</li>
    <li><strong>Casual Atmosphere:</strong> Great for building confidence and overcoming the fear of speaking.</li>
    <li><strong>Lesson Recording:</strong> All calls are recorded automatically so you can review them later.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">Cons of Cambly</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
    <li><strong>Higher Cost:</strong> One of the more expensive platforms on a per-minute basis.</li>
    <li><strong>Tutor Qualifications:</strong> Many tutors are casual conversation partners rather than certified teachers.</li>
    <li><strong>Structure:</strong> Can feel a bit repetitive if you do not have a specific goal in mind.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-20 mb-8 text-center">The Big Comparison Table</h2>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-12">
