  </div>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-16 mb-4">Which One Fits Your Learner Profile?</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Still not sure? Let us look at three common types of learners:</p>
  
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">
    <div class="p-6 border border-slate-700 rounded-xl bg-slate-800/40">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">The Budget Student</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">You need to save money but want real practice. Go with <strong>iTalki</strong>. You can find "Community Tutors" for under $8/hour who are great for conversation.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-6 border border-slate-700 rounded-xl bg-slate-800/40">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">The Career Professional</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">You need to sound professional and track your progress. Go with <strong>Preply</strong>. Their business curriculum and structured plans are worth the investment.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-6 border border-slate-700 rounded-xl bg-slate-800/40">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">The Busy Parent</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">You only have 15 minutes while the kids are asleep. Go with <strong>Cambly</strong>. The instant access means you never waste a spare minute.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-16 mb-4">Final Verdict: Our Top Pick</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-300 mb-12 leading-relaxed">If we have to pick just one for the average English learner in 2026, it is <strong>iTalki</strong>. The combination of price flexibility, the massive variety of tutors, and the lack of a forced subscription makes it the most user-friendly choice. However, if you prefer a structured path and do not mind a subscription, <strong>Preply</strong> is a very close second.</p>

